document_data.Habitat/Society:
The [[outer plane]]s served as the natural home of these creatures, though they could be summoned anywhere by sha'irs and genies.

Once summoned, a marrashi would attempt to increase their numbers in secrecy with the hopes that their offspring would avenge their servitude.

A large body of marrash was employed by the [[yak folk]] of the [[World Pillar Mountains]] to help maintain control and order throughout their [[Yikarian Empire|empire]].{{Cite dragon/241/Campaign Classics: The Roof of the World}}
